@startuml Component Diagram - Layer 4: Infrastructure Services (Simplified)
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml
title Layer 4: Infrastructure Services (6 Essential Utilities)

Container_Boundary(renderer, "Renderer Process (Angular)") {

    Component(ipc_client, "IPC Client", "Service", "Abstraction over Electron Context Bridge\n• Type-safe channels\n• Request/response handling\n• Serialization")
    
    Component(error_handler, "Error Handler", "Service", "Error classification & recovery\n• Validation errors\n• Network errors\n• User errors\n• Recovery strategy")
    
    Component(notification, "Notification Service", "Service", "User feedback channel\n• Toast\n• Snackbar\n• Modal dialogs")

    Component(query_validator, "Query Validator", "Service", "Pre-flight validation\n• Syntax checking\n• Fail-fast\n• Reduces IPC latency")

    Component(performance_monitor, "Performance Monitor", "Service","Operation latency tracking\n• Search response time\n• Import duration\n• SLA monitoring")
    
    Component(audit_logger, "Audit & Logging", "Service", "AGID compliance\n• Operation tracking\n• Event timestamps\n• → Main Process")
}

' Dependencies
Rel(ipc_client, error_handler, "used by")
Rel(ipc_client, audit_logger, "used by")
Rel(error_handler, notification, "notifies")
Rel(error_handler, audit_logger, "logs")
Rel(performance_monitor, audit_logger, "enriches")
Rel(query_validator, ipc_client, "pre-validates")

note as infrastructure
  **Layer 4: Infrastructure**
  
  Essential utilities (6 services):
  
  IPC Client:
  • Single point touching Electron APIs
  • Type-safe channel abstraction
  • Dependency Inversion: services depend on interface, not implementation
  
  Error Handler:
  • Centralized error classification
  • Coordinates error recovery
  • Bridges to notification & logging
  
  Notification Service:
  • Consistent user feedback
  • Single source for toasts/modals
  • UX consistency
  
  Query Validator:
  • Local validation before IPC
  • Fail-fast reduces latency
  • Performance optimization
  
  Performance Monitor:
  • Measures operation timing
  • Tracks SLA compliance
  • Enriches audit logs with metrics
  
  Audit Logger:
  • AGID compliance requirement
  • All user operations logged
  • Timestamps + context
  • Sent to Main Process for persistence
  
  REMOVED (unnecessary):
  ✗ Cache Service (in services directly)
  ✗ Filter Service (Main Process)
  ✗ Theme Service (CSS-based)
  ✗ Accessibility Service (components)
end note

@enduml
